			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Rytan's comments:
<br />

<br />
Asking for any abilities specifically aimed at soloing is going to be a hard sell for me, as I don't think soloing should be an equally lucrative way of gaining experience compared to grouping. 
<br />

<br />
Me: I take it then that your attitude is towards ALL classes and not just Mages.  So let's just look at the following: Pet Heals per second.  We all know the following Math - but Rytan, neither you or anyone else from SOE has ever sought to explain it to anyone playing the game.
<br />

<br />
Both a Beastlord and a Mage can play pet cleric.  Let's look at the efficiency of just this.  What's the expected lifespan of a pet ?
<br />

<br />
BST Heal: 2100 hitpoints in 11.25 secs or 186 hp per second.
<br />
Mage Heal: 1200 hitpoints in 14.5 secs or 82 hp per second.
<br />

<br />
Now lets factor in Slow.  At 65, the Bst gets a 65% slow.  Thus the mob attacks at 35% of it's normal DPS.  Dividing 186 hp per second by 35% equals 533 DPS.  So a Bst can solo any mob that has a natural DPS less than 533 simply by playing pet cleric.  Yes, he may only be able to cast the heal 10 times before OOM, but that would be 112.5 secs of pet life.  The less the natural DPS of the mob, the longer the Bst can be a pet cleric. 
<br />

<br />
Rytan, you love to run mathematical equations on us Mages (see Pet Canni), so plz tell me how long my pet will last against a mob that hits for 533 DPS?  My guess is about 6 secs.  Considering the 7 sec cast time of my pet heal spell I better start casting it before my pet even gets hit.  And then that 1200 point heal will buy me another whopping 2.5 sec of pet life.  So with perfect excecution my pet lives for 8.5 secs versus the Beastlords 112.5 secs.  Great real, where's the class balance?  These 2#'s aren't even in the same universe of each other.  It's not like I can nuke enough in 6 secs to kill a mob, so plz don't start giving me the "well you can nuke" answer.
<br />

<br />
Why does SOE control what each PC's DPS is and make sure everyone is in the right place/ranking, but does nothing when it comes to us dealing with damage done to us?
<br />

<br />
Also, please tell us why asking for any abilities aimed at soloing is such a hard sell, when you've already given the above ability to Beastlords?  You're attitude should be: Ok Mages, we've inadvertainly given Beastlords a ridiculously overpowering combination of spells.  We're nerfing it because they're solo experience should be similiar to yours OR what would you like to be added to your class such that you can have a defense against mobs that hit for 533 DPS?
<br />

<br />
Beastlords ALREADY get 65% damage mitigation thru Slow.  In GoD you're offering us 10%.  And that's fair?  Maybe shared health should work the opposite way.  Maybe we should be able to toggle it.
<br />

<br />
It's nice that you've started to respond to us Mages.  Hopefully, you won't just respond to the easy issues.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
