				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Maleviar (and all),
<br />

<br />
While others may want to drag Beastlords into the discussion, I was simply trying to show one aspect of soloing - pet survivalability.  And I didn't ask for slow or snare.  Please read my comments again.  In fact I suggested that maybe Shared Health should work the opposite as its intended.  Or maybe have a toggle to it.  I proposed a uniquely Mage solution and did not try and make us a Beastlord.  I didn't ask for us to become Beastlords or Necros.  I pointed our that our pet survival is so short that we can't nuke things dead AND that our pet survival is 1/20 that of Beastlords - the other pet class that actually melees a mob rather than snare/aggro kite it.  We're being given Pet Damage Mitigation as an AA in GoD and no other class is.  How would you compare the effectiveness of that ability then since no one else gets it?  I'm trying to show that Beastlords effectively get a 65% damage mitigation now and how that has a radically different effect than 10% damage mitigation thru an AA.  Can I compare the pet damage mitigation AA with a Necro when their pets never take damage?  So please understand I was using a frame of reference for how to judge the eventual solution to mages being able to solo somewhat.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
