				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My whole point is that I think you are all barking up the wrong tree when you bring beastlords and slow into the equation. 
<br />

<br />
You want solo, I get that. I understand it, and I have no problems with the idea. But I don't see why you don't compare mage soloing to wizard, enchanter, druid, bard, shaman, necromancer and shadowknight soloing.
<br />

<br />
Of those listed, the only one who might rely on slow as much as beastlords is shaman. (and enchanters to a lesser extent.)
<br />

<br />
All of those other classes with the possible exception of the shadowknight can solo harder hitting mobs due to a variety of reasons such as...
<br />
A)Better slow (shaman +chanter)
<br />
B)Better heals (shaman and druid)
<br />
C)Better mana regen (shaman, necro, wizard)
<br />
D)Never getting hit by the mob!!!!(Druid, necro, shadowknight, wizard, bard.)
<br />

<br />
This list isn't completely accurate, but it's a good indication. If you want to solo well, the best bet is never getting hit by the mobs. Hence, the best answer to mitigating the 533 dps of an unslowed mob is not to give mages slow, but snare.
<br />

<br />

<br />
