			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Maleviar,
<br />

<br />
Zyphyr has already posted on the soloing styles of other classes.  Beastlords solo in a style similiar to Mages and the other classes don't.  I've never asked for snare or slow.  We're getting an AA ability that causes allows for 10% damage mitigation.  We're also getting a Shard Health AA.  I'm not looking for us to start soloing in the way all the other classes do.  I'd like to solo in a style similiar to the one I've always used.  It doesn't have to be as efficient in terms of exp/hr as grouping.  But if I go all out, I'd like to be able to kill a dark blue con once in a while.  My specific suggestion is to improve the 2 new AA we are getting because you don't have to be in GoD beta to know it isn't really going to make a difference.  Our pet damage mitigation needs to be MUCH HIGHER than 10%.  Why it isn't 65-70% (which is the top end slow) is ridiculous to me.  If Sony is afraid of our pets becoming raid MA's, then give us an AA that maxes at 65% damage mitigation on Dark Blue cons, 40% Damage Mitigation on even cons and, 25% Damage mitigation on yellow cons and 10% Damage Mitigation on Red Cons.  Now isn't this a uniquely Mage solution?  Wouldn't this provide the Mage class with an adequate soloing experience when compared to the other classes yet not just simply adopt their playstyles?  Now combine this with Shared Health.  Why can't we take some of the Damage our Pet takes?  If we can offload damage done to us on the pet, then why not the other way? We have a strong bond with our pets, let's re-enforce it.  And just think about the Raid utility of all this - we would be wanted in a raiding force for OffTanking all those DB cons that show up.  I think our 2 new AA are in the right direction - I just think they are completely underpowered when compared to what the game already is.  Rytan, I hope your listening because I really like the idea of pet damage mitigation in proportion to how the mob cons and I don't think it causes any imbalance in soloing, grouping or raiding.  Sure, playtest and change the #'s around cause I just threw some out, but I think the idea has a lot of merit.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
