			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Why compare mages to beastlords?  Lvl 65, all spells but with 0 aa.  
<br />

<br />

<br />
Mob: 15,000HP, 150DPS output to pet
<br />

<br />
v/s mage: Fully geared WoX @ 53dps, alternate Sun Vortex & Planar Renewal in a 14sec cycle.  85hp/sec heals to pet results in cutting mob dps to 65dps - or increases the max duration of the fight to 73 + 10 secs for enrage.   This results in almost 6 cycles, for which the pet has been healed 12,600HP and the mage has done 9300dmg via SV + 4399dmg from pet.  Result= expended 1800mana in heals, 2370mana in nukes, and 70mana via gate.  90 second rush that will take 11 minutes to recover to FM, then an additional 4 minutes to re-summon new gear and pet.  This is of course only true if said mage had a 4200+ mana pool, else would have gated sooner.
<br />

<br />
v/s bst: Fully geared warder $ 51dps, mob slowed 65% resulting in pet taking 53dps.  Beastlord can now heal warder once per 45 seconds, resulting in pet taking 0 damage overall while the beastlord loses 10 mana per second standing, 6 mana/second sitting.  With a 3k mana pool, they can do this for 500 seconds (8.33 minutes) until OOM.  But, they only need to last 294 seconds when their pet lands the killing blow i.e. 4.9 minutes - leaving them 30% mana, taking 6 minutes to med to full and do it all over again.
<br />

<br />
Mage = 16.5 minutes ordeal, resulting in death or 0 gain.
<br />
Beastlord = 10.9 minutes xp grind, rdy to do it again.
<br />

<br />
Why don't I compare necro?  Because they don't have the balls to stand toe-to-toe against mobs.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=501504">Anthe Battlecaster</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
