			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was the one who brought up the soloing style of other classes. I had assumed it was such common knowledge how they solo  that I didn't spell out the specific method each class uses.
<br />

<br />
However, apparently, you've missed my point. They ALL (except maybe SK's) solo for better exp than mages.
<br />

<br />
Can you understand my point? Here's a dramatization for you...
<br />

<br />
SOE: Ok, mages, we've decided to give you better soloing ability. Now, under the proper circumstances, wizards, druids, bards, necromancers, shamans, and shadowknights can all solo for better experience than a full group. They do this by manipulating distance with the mob so in effect it doesn't matter if the mob hits for 100 dps or 1 million dps. 
<br />

<br />
Mage: I want slow like beastlord.
<br />

<br />
SOE: Well, even if we gave you that, you'd solo for at best about 50% of the exp you'd get in an average group. And let's not forget that there would be an effective cap on the difficulty of the mob you'd be able to solo, and that cap would be the mob's DPS vs. your ability to heal your pet. 
<br />

<br />
Mage: I want slow.
<br />

<br />
SOE: Well, what about snare? Shadowknights have been known to solo some large mobs using high aggro spells and their ridiculously low level pet. You'd be able to kill bigger mobs in higher level planes than any beastlord ever would, with the chance for better loot.
<br />

<br />
Mage: I want slow.
<br />

<br />
SOE: Well...if that's what you want, I hereby grant you Elemental Lethargy. Yep, that's right, it works on all 6 elemental mobs in the game. You know the ones I'm talking about, the level 25'ish mobs in Sol A? I don't believe they'll be giving you problems any time soon!
<br />

<br />
Look, take it from a BST. Slow is not the answer for good soloing. Yes, it helps, but there are better ways. Sticking to the idea of soloing mobs toe to toe is cutting off your nose to spite your face. There are better ways. In fact, almost any method of soloing planes mobs is better than going toe to toe.
<br />

<br />
Quick edit: About the 65% mitigation idea vs. blues. Well, if a mage pet mitigated 65% vs. blues without slow, then would that not lead itself to being ridiculously overpowerd in a group? 65% mitigation combined with a 65-75% slowed mob? Quick math...example mob A does 1000dps, slowed 75% does 250dps, 65% mitigated by mage pet who is now group MA does, let's see...87.5 dps....Anyone else see a problem here?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
