			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Fine slow isn't the BEST answer for us.  So give us something else.  Would snare be great? Of course.  It's the staple spell for every other class in terms of efficient soloing.  So I'm not at all against Mages getting a snare.  Or give the Earth pet a Root and Snare, so when the Root wears off there's still a Snare.  But the fact in the end remains that SOE isnt giving us Snare.  What are they giving us - Damage Mitigation and Shared Health.  Can we solo with these?  Well, IMHO not much better than we solo now.  If they upped the power of one or both of these then maybe.  And if in a group the combination of slow and damage mitigation is too much, then only have the pet mitigate damage if you're not group.  But even in the present system, a mob isn't going to aggro on a pet if there are multiple entities on it's aggro list.  So there are ways around it.  Very simply we should get snare in some fashion.  But they don't want Mages to solo that way, maybe because they already have too many classes that do it.  So we need to find ways to solo in the framework of what they're offering us.  Personally, I think the MS4 pet should have kept the snare/slow procs and the fire pet should have become the raid pet.  But that's too logical for SOE.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
